{
  "name": "Glazed Apple Fritter",
  "description": "Two single-serve baked apple fritters on an AP-flour/protein base — real butter, REAL brown sugar (2 tbsp, for molasses and moisture), cinnamon and nutmeg in the crumb, finished with a PROTEIN glaze (whey + Fairlife milk + Splenda) that sets like real icing instead of a thin sugar drizzle. The protein-glaze upgrade is borrowed from the Apple Fritter Bites. House calibration: sweeteners are granulated Splenda except the batter brown sugar; eggs are medium.",
  "tags": [
    "apple-fritter",
    "protein",
    "baked",
    "glazed"
  ],
  "yield": {
    "amount": 2,
    "unit": "fritters"
  },
  "content": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "componentKey": "b1",
        "order": 1,
        "section": "fritter",
        "instructionText": "Mix the Greek yogurt, melted butter, and brown sugar. Stir in the flour, protein, baking powder, cinnamon, and nutmeg, then fold in the diced apple."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "b2",
        "order": 2,
        "section": "fritter",
        "instructionText": "Preheat to 350F. Shape the batter into 2 fritter rounds on a greased sheet and bake 10-12 min. Cool 10 min.",
        "temperature": 350
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "g1",
        "order": 3,
        "section": "glaze",
        "instructionText": "Whisk the protein powder, Splenda, Fairlife milk, and vanilla into a thick, pourable glaze (add a few drops more milk only if needed). Drizzle over the cooled fritters and let it set 5-10 min — unlike a water glaze, the protein glaze firms into a real icing."
      }
    ],
